race.comment: RARE MOON (7) backs up 10 days after racing on the speed and finishing second over 1300m at Toowoomba. Strong run last time and is expected to go well again. MISTER MIGHTY (10) could only manage sixth on debut then improved last start but found one better over 1350m at Warwick, beaten 3.5 lengths after being in contention on the corner. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. WHAT DID YOU SAY (4) started at $9 last time and ran below expectations, finishing eighth and beaten 8 lengths at Gold Coast over 1400m after being prominent at the bend. Won't find this as tough so he is perfectly placed to score. KING MAL (1) finished 14 lengths away in 11th at his last appearance over 1400m at Sunshine Coast on October 19 after he gave away a big start. Among the chances in what looks a nice race for him.
